title: Top White House aide makes secret trip to Ukraine amid U.S. aid impasse
description: National security adviser Jake Sullivan is in Ukraine for high-level meetings as a multibillion-dollar U.S. aid package remains stalled in Congress.

title: A U.K. man sent unwanted nudes. He’s going to prison under a new law.
description: Nicholas Hawkes, 39, was sentenced to 66 weeks in prison after sending photos of his genitals to a 15-year-old girl and a woman on WhatsApp.

title: History of royal portrait retouching includes chins lifted, waists cinched
description: Heavy editing of royal photos was common when the public had somewhat different expectations about authenticity and when media outlets had different standards.

title: Blinken begins new round of Gaza talks in Saudi Arabia
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken started a visit to Saudi Arabia, Egypt and Israel to discuss the future of Gaza with regional leaders on Wednesday.

title: Texas immigration law back in federal court after whiplash rulings
description: An appeals panel will hear arguments Wednesday about whether to keep blocking a Texas law that allows local police to arrest and deport undocumented migrants.

title: America’s happiness score drops amid a youth ‘midlife crisis’
description: The United States is no longer among the world’s 20 happiest countries, according to the World Happiness Report 2024 — with young people hit particularly hard.

title: Cease-fire still elusive, but observers say Hamas position may be easing
description: After weeks of demanding a permanent cease-fire, Hamas appears to be open to an initial pause in fighting and the exchange of some hostages for prisoners.

title: Leo Varadkar, Irish prime minister, announces ‘surprise’ resignation
description: When Varadkar assumed the office in 2017, he made history as the youngest, first openly gay and first person from an ethnic-minority background to lead Ireland.

title: U.K. watchdog assessing potential breach of Princess Kate’s medical records
description: Britain’s privacy watchdog said it was assessing a potential breach of the medical records of Catherine, Princess of Wales, while at the London Clinic.

title: She made an artwork that excluded men. A man sued for discrimination.
description: The Ladies Lounge at a prominent Australian museum includes Picassos and antiquities, but the space’s core artistic act is excluding men, its creator said.

title: Only seven countries met WHO air standards in 2023, report says
description: Few countries met World Health Organization standards for PM 2.5 pollution, the most dangerous kind for human health. The United States was not one of them.

title: Delta pilot intoxicated before N.Y. flight jailed for 10 months in Scotland
description: Lawrence B. Russell Jr. was caught carrying a half-empty bottle of Jägermeister in his luggage before he was set to fly a Boeing 767 from Edinburgh to New York.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Netanyahu remains set on Rafah operation, despite U.S. pressure
description: The U.S. is set to host an Israeli delegation to discuss Israel’s plans to send forces into Rafah, a city in southern Gaza where Palestinians have sought refuge.

title: Ukraine races to manufacture weapons at home
description: Ukraine had virtually no domestic weapons industry when Russia invaded and the country is quickly ramping up production but lack of money and a shortage of gunpowder pose challenges.

title: How the war in Ukraine has split the Czechs and Slovaks
description: The marked differences between a staunchly pro-Kyiv government in Prague and Slovakia’s Russia-friendly Prime Minister Robert Fico have come to the fore.

title: Rose Dugdale, English heiress who became IRA militant, dies at 82
description: In 1958, she was a debutante at a Buckingham Palace ball. In 1974, she was masterminding plots for the Irish Republican Army.
